gomodel:SYNGO_1695  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig 3 GKAP is closely associated with the dense material at the core of the PSD complex\nLiteral: \"Pre-embedding immunogold electron microscopy was conducted on hippocampal cultures, using antibodies for GKAP and Shank. GKAP antibody was against a C-terminal peptide containing the binding site for Shank, while pan Shank antibody was raised against a peptide that includes the sequence for its PDZ domain, the binding site for GKAP. PSDs of asymmetric\nsynapses showed prominent labeling for both GKAP and Shank (Fig. 3).. Experimental description: Hippocampal rat neuronal cultures\nLiteral from M&M:\n\"Hippocampal cells from 21-day embryonic Sprague-Dawley rats were dissociated and grown on a feeder layer of glial cells for 3-4 weeks." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1695" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

